[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it possible to disable <code>linter.unusedTactic</code> and <code>linter.unreachableTactic</code> in proofs with error? When there is an error on some line, every next line gets flagged with <code>linter.unreachableTactic</code> which is unhelpful and quite distracting. The same line also gets flagged by <code>linter.unusedTactic</code> which is just wrong because it did do something: create an error.<br>\nA typical example:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/IvT80LL2bFoP3VY1S1SQw1cb/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/IvT80LL2bFoP3VY1S1SQw1cb/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1070x390\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/IvT80LL2bFoP3VY1S1SQw1cb/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 513718146,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1745352245
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Probably some <code>set_option</code></p>",
        "id": 513718254,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1745352278
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would hope this could be done globally. I think remembering a magic spell and casting it whenever you want to fix some proof isn't really user friendly.</p>",
        "id": 513718530,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1745352369
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe if you put it in your lakefile</p>",
        "id": 513718610,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1745352404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is a v4.19.0 regression FYI</p>",
        "id": 513718662,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1745352425
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think if you have</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">lean_lib</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">leanOptions</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"o\">[</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">...</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"ss\">`linter.unusedTactic</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"ss\">`linter.unreachableTactic</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">...</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>in your lakefile it will disable it globally</p>",
        "id": 513719325,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1745352699
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(not tested)</p>",
        "id": 513719353,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1745352713
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Previously the linter would abort early if the proof reported that there was a <code>sorry</code></p>",
        "id": 513719481,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1745352764
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The point is to disable it globally for errored proof only.</p>",
        "id": 513719508,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1745352776
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What you ask for is how it always behaved in older versions</p>",
        "id": 513719563,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1745352800
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/8101\">lean4#8101</a> is meant to fix this</p>",
        "id": 515514989,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
